subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks. This species is similar to
Calepitrimerus rosarum
Lin & Kuang, 2001
b, but can be differentiated by dorsal annuli with elliptical microtubercles on dorsal ridges (dorsal annuli smooth in
C . rosarum
), empodium 4 -rayed, tarsal solenidion knobbed (empodium 5 -rayed, tarsal solenidion tapered in
C . rosarum
), middorsal ridges long (middorsal ridges short in
C . rosarum
).
